We have also studied the links between the cryosphere and the carbon cycle through the mid-Pleistocene Transition</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>Both the data and the modelling results will be of use to a wide range of researchers. In particular the data will be of use to those studying the sensitivity of the Antarctic ice sheet to environmental change.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>091E0853-27F8-4861-9F4D-C3D9C8BDEB54</gtr:id><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Environment</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/01646E97-0D14-41EA-A204-7AA7D926464C"><gtr:id>01646E97-0D14-41EA-A204-7AA7D926464C</gtr:id><gtr:title>The relative roles of CO
